ON SOBRIETY, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

05:40.458 --> 05:42.792
AND THEN YOU LECTURE ABOUT
SAFE SEX, OFFER TO PUT IN ONE OF

05:42.834 --> 05:44.959
THOSE IMPLANT-Y BIRTH CONTROL
THINGS THAT GO IN HER ARM,

05:45.000 --> 05:46.709
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH,
SHE WILL REFUSE,

05:46.750 --> 05:48.291
THEN YOU WILL DELIVER THE BABY,

05:48.333 --> 05:50.291
AND THEN PETE,
BECAUSE SHE ONLY LIKES PETE,

05:50.333 --> 05:53.542
WILL GIVE HER $50,
AND SHE'LL GIVE US THE BABY.
WELL, SHE LIKES ME

05:53.583 --> 05:56.208
BECAUSE I'VE HELPED HER GET
CLEAN, WHAT, LIKE, THREE TIMES?
YEAH.

05:56.250 --> 05:59.208
NOT THAT IT EVER LASTS
MORE THAN A WEEK.
ANYWAY, IT SHOULDN'T TAKE
TOO LONG.

05:59.250 --> 06:01.583
I'LL GET SOCIAL SERVICES
ON THE PHONE,

06:01.625 --> 06:04.542
LET 'EM KNOW
WE GOT ONE COMING.
OKAY, I'LL GET THE PAPERWORK
FOR HER TO SIGN.

06:04.583 --> 06:06.625
SO YOU WANT
TO EXAMINE HER FIRST,

06:06.667 --> 06:10.041
OR YOU WANT ME TO DO
MY SHRINK DANCE FIRST?
WHAT?

06:10.083 --> 06:13.041
COOPER. HEY.

06:13.083 --> 06:15.417
NAOMI. WELCOME BACK. HEY.

06:15.458 --> 06:19.542
I AM SO SORRY I COULDN'T COME
WHEN I HEARD ABOUT CHARLOTTE.

06:19.583 --> 06:21.625
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

06:21.667 --> 06:23.875
WE, UH, WE'RE GOOD.
YEAH?

06:23.917 --> 06:26.041
OKAY. DEALING.

06:26.083 --> 06:27.542
YEAH.

06:27.583 --> 06:29.583
OH, MY GOD.
LOOK, JUSTIN TAYLOR.

06:29.625 --> 06:32.583
YEAH?
I HAVEN'T SEEN THIS KID
IN, LIKE, THREE YEARS.

06:32.625 --> 06:34.625
I THOUGHT HE HAD MOVED
OR SOMETHING. HE'S...

06:34.667 --> 06:36.875
HE'S ONE OF THE GOOD ONES.

06:36.917 --> 06:38.875
HE USED TO MAKE ME
THESE GREAT MIX CDs--

06:38.917 --> 06:40.667
DR. FREEDMAN.

06:40.709 --> 06:43.000
IT'S ME, JUSTIN.

06:52.083 --> 06:54.667
I BROUGHT YOU
THIS PLAYLIST.
OH, YEAH?

06:54.709 --> 06:56.458
ALL SICK INDIE BANDS,

06:56.500 --> 06:58.041
INCLUDING DEATH FINGER'S
NEW TRACK.

06:58.083 --> 07:00.709
AWESOME. THANK YOU.
HEY, HOW'D YOU GET HERE?

07:00.750 --> 07:03.041
I TOOK THE BUS.

07:03.083 --> 07:05.417
AND YOUR PARENTS,
DO THEY KNOW YOU'RE HERE?

07:05.458 --> 07:08.458
I-I DIDN'T WANT TO BOTHER THEM.
THEY'RE BUSY, YOU KNOW, AT WORK.

07:08.500 --> 07:10.959
OKAY, OKAY.
(inhales deeply)

07:11.000 --> 07:12.500
JUSTIN, I'M CONCERNED

07:12.542 --> 07:14.500
BECAUSE YOU'VE GAINED
A LOT OF WEIGHT

07:14.542 --> 07:17.500
SINCE THE LAST TIME I SAW YOU--
A SIGNIFICANT AMOUNT OF WEIGHT.

07:17.542 --> 07:19.500
I KNOW.
I KEEP GETTING BIGGER,

07:19.542 --> 07:21.500
AND IT'S GOTTEN HARDER
TO GET AROUND,

07:21.542 --> 07:23.500
LIKE, A LOT HARDER
JUST RECENTLY.

07:23.542 --> 07:26.542
OKAY. CAN YOU
GET ON THE SCALE FOR ME?

07:26.583 --> 07:30.000
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S JUST YOU AND ME.

07:35.083 --> 07:36.709
(grunts)

07:36.750 --> 07:38.125
(exhales)

07:42.291 --> 07:44.709
(scale squeaks)

07:50.291 --> 07:52.500
HOW MUCH?

07:52.542 --> 07:55.583
YOU'VE GAINED 282 POUNDS.

07:55.625 --> 07:57.375
OH, MAN.

07:57.417 --> 07:59.375
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

07:59.417 --> 08:03.500
WE JUST NEED TO TALK ABOUT IT,
OKAY? COME ON.

08:03.542 --> 08:05.500
AND HOW MANY WEEKS ALONG
ARE YOU?

08:05.542 --> 08:07.041
UH, EIGHT MONTHS MAYBE.

08:07.083 --> 08:09.709
HOW MANY WEEKS IS THAT?
I'M NOT SO GOOD WITH MATH.

08:09.750 --> 08:11.291
OR PRENATAL CARE.

08:11.333 --> 08:14.375
ARE YOU TAKING ANY
PRENATAL VITAMINS THIS TIME?

08:14.417 --> 08:17.041
GETTING EXAMS AT ANY OF THOSE
FREE CLINICS WE TOLD YOU ABOUT?

08:17.083 --> 08:20.959
I'VE BEEN BUSY.
THE ULTRASOUND PUTS THE BABY
AT 37 WEEKS.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.083
HEARTBEAT'S STRONG.

08:23.125 --> 08:25.792
BUT YOUR PRESSURE IS STILL
A LITTLE ON THE HIGH SIDE,

08:25.834 --> 08:28.208
SO I'D LIKE TO KEEP YOU
OVERNIGHT FOR OBSERVATION.

08:28.250 --> 08:29.709
BECAUSE THE BABY IS BREECH,

08:29.750 --> 08:32.583
WE'LL HAVE TO DO
A C-SECTION TOMORROW.
OKAY.

08:32.625 --> 08:35.041
LOOKS LIKE YOU GET THREE HOTS
AND A COT THIS TIME, EMILY.

08:35.083 --> 08:37.291
SO I WILL TELL DR. KING
TO HOLD OFF D.C.F.S.

08:37.333 --> 08:40.333
FOR PICKING UP THE BABY
TILL TOMORROW.
NO. I DON'T WANT
D.C.F.S. TO COME.

08:40.375 --> 08:43.041
I DIDN'T ASK YOU TO DO THAT.

08:43.083 --> 08:45.375
LOOK, THOSE OTHER TIMES,
I WAS AN ADDICT.

08:45.417 --> 08:47.834
I-I DIDN'T HAVE A PLACE TO LIVE.
I HAD ISSUES.
(laughs) YOU HAD ISSUES?

08:47.875 --> 08:49.834
YOU CAN'T TAKE AWAY
THIS BABY.

08:49.875 --> 08:52.792
I GOT CLEAN A MONTH OR TWO
BEFORE I EVEN GOT KNOCKED UP,

08:52.834 --> 08:55.750
AND--AND I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO QUIT SMOKING.

08:55.792 --> 08:57.750
I SWEAR.
DO ANY DRUG TEST YOU WANT.

08:57.792 --> 09:00.041
LOOK, THIS BABY, IT'S GONNA BE
HEALTHY, AND I WANT TO KEEP IT.

09:00.083 --> 09:02.667
EMILY,
THAT IS NOT A GOOD IDEA.
I'LL DO WHATEVER YOU WANT.
PLEASE.

09:02.709 --> 09:04.667
I WANT TO KEEP THIS BABY.

09:04.709 --> 09:07.375
DR. MONTGOMERY, PLEASE DON'T
LET HER TAKE AWAY MY BABY.

09:07.417 --> 09:10.625
NO ONE IS GONNA TAKE AWAY
YOUR BABY. OKAY?

09:10.667 --> 09:14.208
I'M GONNA HELP YOU.

09:22.667 --> 09:25.041
HELLO, MR. AND MRS. TAYLOR.

09:25.083 --> 09:27.458
I'M DR. BENNETT.

09:27.500 --> 09:30.625
HOW IS IT POSSIBLE
THAT HE IS THIS FAT?

09:30.667 --> 09:32.500
(Naomi) UH, WELL, WE--
WE ARE CONCERNED.

09:32.542 --> 09:36.417
JUSTIN IS DIABETIC,
AND HE HAS HIGH BLOOD PRESSURE.

09:36.458 --> 09:38.166
AND THAT PUTS HIM AT RISK

09:38.208 --> 09:40.709
FOR EVEN MORE
SERIOUS MEDICAL COMPLICATIONS.

09:40.750 --> 09:42.625
HE'S LAZY AND HE DOESN'T
WANT TO LOSE WEIGHT.

09:42.667 --> 09:45.166
I HAVE NO CONTROL OVER
WHAT HE DOES OR DOESN'T DO.

09:45.208 --> 09:47.875
YOU'RE HIS PARENTS.
THAT'S YOUR JOB.

09:47.917 --> 09:49.834
WHAT DR. FREEDMAN MEANS
IS THAT

09:49.875 --> 09:52.709
JUSTIN NEEDS PROPER NUTRITION
AND EXERCISE

09:52.750 --> 09:56.083
AND MEDICATION COMPLIANCE
TO GET HIS HEALTH BACK ON TRACK.

09:56.125 --> 09:58.333
WE SENT HIM TO FAT CAMP,
WE HIRED A NUTRITIONIST,

09:58.375 --> 10:00.625
AND WE GOT HIM A TRAINER.

10:00.667 --> 10:04.709
COULD IT BE A THYROID CONDITION
OR A TUMOR ON SOME GLAND?

10:04.750 --> 10:06.709
WE RAN TESTS AND RULED OUT

10:06.750 --> 10:08.834
ANY UNDERLYING CAUSES
FOR THE WEIGHT GAIN.

10:08.875 --> 10:11.041
I DON'T WANT
TO GET ANY BIGGER.

10:11.083 --> 10:12.542
I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

10:12.583 --> 10:14.333
(Mr. Taylor) HE SNEAKS FOOD.

10:14.375 --> 10:16.667
I FIND CANDY WRAPPERS
UNDER YOUR BED ALL THE TIME.

10:16.709 --> 10:19.041
HE'S TRYING, BRUCE.
(Cooper) LOOK,
COULD WE JUST STOP

10:19.083 --> 10:21.625
AND TRY TO BE CONSTRUCTIVE?
ARE YOU STILL
GONNA BE SAYING THAT

10:21.667 --> 10:24.041
WHEN HE'S 600 POUNDS,
DR. FREEDMAN?

10:24.083 --> 10:26.333
I MEAN, I-I'D PUT A LOCK
ON THE FRIDGE

10:26.375 --> 10:29.875
IF I DIDN'T THINK
HE'D EAT IT OFF.
JUSTIN?

10:29.917 --> 10:33.250
ARE YOU OKAY?
I FEEL A LITTLE DIZZY.

10:33.291 --> 10:35.041
JUSTIN.

10:35.083 --> 10:36.542
(exhales)
JUSTIN!

10:38.750 --> 10:40.875
(Cooper)
HIS PULSE IS SKY HIGH.

10:40.917 --> 10:43.041
YEAH.
I'LL GET OXYGEN.

10:43.083 --> 10:44.583
OKAY.
(beeps)

10:44.625 --> 10:47.083
GET ME AN I.V. CART
AND CALL AN AMBULANCE, PLEASE.

10:47.125 --> 10:48.709
HERE.

10:50.208 --> 10:52.667
PEOPLE CAN CHANGE, VIOLET.
I KNOW YOU BELIEVE THAT.

10:52.709 --> 10:55.625
WHY NOT EMILY?
WE HAVE TRIED, ADDISON,
AGAIN AND AGAIN.

10:55.667 --> 10:58.166
BUT IT WON'T TAKE
BECAUSE SHE DOESN'T WANT IT TO.

10:58.208 --> 11:00.959
TEN MINUTES AFTER I GET HER
CLEAN, SHE GOES OUT TO SCORE.

11:01.000 --> 11:03.083
I-I BEG A SHELTER
TO FIND A BED FOR HER,

11:03.125 --> 11:06.041
AND SHE NEVER SHOWS UP.
THE BEST THING WOULD BE
IF SHE STOPPED

11:06.083 --> 11:08.041
HAVING BABIES ALTOGETHER.
WE SHOULD TIE HER TUBES.

11:08.083 --> 11:11.000
YOU'RE DOING HER C-SECTION
TOMORROW. YOU COULD DO IT THEN.

11:11.041 --> 11:14.000
I AM NOT GONNA STERILIZE A WOMAN
WITHOUT HER KNOWLEDGE.

11:14.041 --> 11:16.542
I NEED HER CONSENT.
WELL, IT'S THE ONLY WAY
TO KEEP HER

11:16.583 --> 11:19.041
FROM COMING BACK PREGNANT
IN A YEAR.
OKAY, OKAY, LOOK,
EMILY IS A DISASTER.

11:19.083 --> 11:21.041
NO ONE WANTS TO SEE
HER COMING BACK PREGNANT,

11:21.083 --> 11:23.041
BUT ADDISON IS RIGHT.

11:23.083 --> 11:26.041
SHE HAS TO SIGN OFF
ON THE STERILIZATION.
JUST BECAUSE EMILY'S MADE
BAD DECISIONS

11:26.083 --> 11:29.333
DOESN'T MEAN THAT WE TAKE AWAY
HER RIGHT TO HAVE CHILDREN.
WHY ARE WE ONLY
DISCUSSING HER RIGHTS?

11:29.375 --> 11:31.542
WHAT ABOUT DAVID'S RIGHTS?
WHO'S DAVID?

11:31.583 --> 11:33.041
HER FIRSTBORN.
EIGHT WEEKS PREMATURE.

11:33.083 --> 11:35.583
HE WENT BLIND
FROM BEING ON A VENTILATOR.

11:35.625 --> 11:37.583
HE'S BEEN IN SEVEN HOMES
IN SIX YEARS.

11:37.625 --> 11:40.208
TURNS OUT HE'S NOT ONLY BLIND.
HE'S AUTISTIC.

11:40.250 --> 11:41.667
BRAD WAS SECOND.

11:41.709 --> 11:43.667
HE'S SEVERELY DISABLED
DUE TO FETAL ALCOHOL SYNDROME.

11:43.709 --> 11:45.667
HE'S IN A HOME
FOR SPECIAL NEEDS KIDS.

11:45.709 --> 11:48.750
THEN THERE'S APRIL, WHO'S--WELL,
SHE'S STILL IN FOSTER CARE,

11:48.792 --> 11:50.959
'CAUSE WHO WANTS A CRACK BABY?
AND THEN... (sighs)

11:51.000 --> 11:52.458
THERE'S DANIEL,

11:52.500 --> 11:55.041
WHO SURVIVED FOR 16
EXCRUCIATING DAYS IN N.I.C.U.

11:55.083 --> 11:57.667
BEFORE HE SUCCUMBED
TO SHORT BOWEL SYNDROME.

11:57.709 --> 12:00.000
I SIGNED
HIS DEATH CERTIFICATE MYSELF.
YOU THINK SHE WANTS
THIS BABY?

12:00.041 --> 12:02.834
SHE DOESN'T WANT THIS BABY.
SHE HAS AN ANGLE.

12:02.875 --> 12:06.041
SHE ALWAYS HAS AN ANGLE.
SHE'S NOT GONNA CHANGE,
ADDISON. TIE HER TUBES.

12:06.083 --> 12:08.041
WITHOUT HER CONSENT, I CAN'T.

12:08.083 --> 12:10.542
I'M SORRY.
I WON'T DO IT.

12:12.667 --> 12:14.208
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

12:14.250 --> 12:16.625
JUSTIN. HOW IS HE?

12:16.667 --> 12:18.875
UM, HIS BLOOD SUGAR SPIKED,

12:18.917 --> 12:20.583
WHICH CAUSED
PROFOUND DEHYDRATION

12:20.625 --> 12:22.041
AND ELECTROLYTE
ABNORMALITIES.

12:22.083 --> 12:24.625
HE'S GONNA WAKE UP, RIGHT?
UH, WELL, YEAH. HE'S--

12:24.667 --> 12:28.166
HE'S A LITTLE BIT DISORIENTED
AND CONFUSED, BUT HE SHOULD

12:28.208 --> 12:30.625
RESPOND TO TREATMENT
WITHIN THE NEXT 12 HOURS.

12:30.667 --> 12:33.250
WE'RE GONNA BRING DOWN
HIS BLOOD SUGAR, BUT SLOWLY.
(Mrs. Taylor)
BUT HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

12:33.291 --> 12:36.667
I MEAN, HE'S NOT GONNA DIE.
(Cooper) WELL, THAT DEPENDS
ON WHAT YOU'RE WILLING TO DO.

12:36.709 --> 12:39.041
HE'S A TEENAGER WITH THE HEALTH
OF A 70 YEAR OLD.

12:39.083 --> 12:40.875
HE COULD STROKE OUT
AT ANY MINUTE.

12:40.917 --> 12:43.333
HE'S AT RISK
FOR A HEART ATTACK.
(Bruce)
YOU CODDLE HIM TOO MUCH.

12:43.375 --> 12:45.041
YOU ALWAYS HAVE.
I LOVE HIM.

12:45.083 --> 12:47.667
I'M NOT LIKE YOU--

12:47.709 --> 12:49.750
THE WAY YOU LOOK AT HIM
WITH SUCH DISGUST.

12:49.792 --> 12:52.083
I MEAN, HOW DO YOU THINK
THAT MAKES HIM FEEL?

12:52.125 --> 12:55.208
OF COURSE HE EATS.
HE NEEDS COMFORT.
WHAT HE NEEDS IS DISCIPLINE.

12:55.250 --> 12:58.667
YOU MAKE HIM THINK IT'S OKAY
TO INHALE ALL THE CRAP HE WANTS.
OKAY, WHY DON'T--

12:58.709 --> 13:00.750
WHY DON'T WE GO INTO THE LOUNGE
AND DISCUSS THIS?

13:00.792 --> 13:03.041
I DON'T WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

13:03.083 --> 13:06.709
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
AROUND MY BABY.

13:06.750 --> 13:09.667
I'M GOING BACK TO WORK.
YOU'RE LEAVING?

13:09.709 --> 13:11.500
(footsteps retreat)

13:11.542 --> 13:14.583
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

13:14.625 --> 13:17.625
(woman speaking indistinctly
over p.a.)

13:19.542 --> 13:22.125
HEY. IS EVERYTHING OKAY HERE?

13:22.166 --> 13:25.542
YEAH. I WAS JUST
CHECKING UP ON EMILY.

13:25.583 --> 13:27.750
YOUR TOX SCREENS
CAME BACK NEGATIVE,

13:27.792 --> 13:29.750
AND YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY S.T.D.s.

13:29.792 --> 13:32.041
I TOLD YOU
THIS BABY WAS HEALTHY.

13:32.083 --> 13:34.750
I'VE BEEN THINKING,
AFTER THE DELIVERY,

13:34.792 --> 13:37.041
YOU SHOULD TIE MY TUBES.

13:37.083 --> 13:40.166
DID YOU COME UP WITH THAT IDEA
ON YOUR OWN?

13:40.208 --> 13:42.917
I'VE JUST BEEN GOING OVER
THE BASICS, THE ANATOMY--

13:42.959 --> 13:45.917
DID HE ALSO EXPLAIN THAT
THIS IS A PERMANENT CHOICE?

13:45.959 --> 13:49.417
THAT'S THE POINT, RIGHT?
EMILY, THERE ARE OTHER FORMS
OF BIRTH CONTROL THAT

13:49.458 --> 13:52.625
WOULD PRESERVE THE OPTION OF
HAVING CHILDREN IN THE FUTURE.
(pager beeps)

13:52.667 --> 13:54.625
WE WENT OVER
ALL THE OPTIONS.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.041
THIS IS HER DECISION.

13:56.083 --> 13:59.500
SORRY. I HAVE TO GET BACK
TO THE E.R.

13:59.542 --> 14:01.583
(door opens)

14:01.625 --> 14:03.583
IF HE PRESSURED YOU
IN ANY WAY, I--

14:03.625 --> 14:05.125
HE DIDN'T.
(door closes)

14:05.166 --> 14:07.041
WHAT HE SAID MAKES SENSE.

14:07.083 --> 14:11.041
AND I WANT TO GIVE THIS BABY
AND ME THE BEST POSSIBLE SHOT.

14:11.083 --> 14:13.750
SO DO IT, DR. MONTGOMERY.

14:13.792 --> 14:17.458
TIE MY TUBES.

14:20.500 --> 14:21.959
YOU THINK PETE BRIBED HER?

14:22.000 --> 14:24.000
THAT'S WHAT THEY DO
WITH EMILY.

14:24.041 --> 14:26.000
THEY GIVE HER MONEY TO GET HER
TO DO WHAT THEY WANT.
WELL, THAT'S ONE WAY
OF HELPING.

14:26.041 --> 14:28.000
WHAT, YOU THINK
SHE SHOULD KEEP THE BABY?

14:28.041 --> 14:30.166
I MEAN, DO YOU THINK
THAT SHE WANTS TO CHANGE?

14:30.208 --> 14:33.583
I WOULD LIKE TO HELP EMILY
IMPROVE HER LIFE.
SO YOU THINK PETE, VIOLET,
AND CHARLOTTE COULDN'T,

14:33.625 --> 14:36.583
BUT--BUT YOU CAN?
I'D LIKE TO TRY.

14:36.625 --> 14:39.583
IS THIS FOR YOUR SAKE
OR FOR HERS?

14:39.625 --> 14:42.250
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

14:45.417 --> 14:46.792
W--

14:49.917 --> 14:51.834
WHAT?

14:51.875 --> 14:54.375
I'M SUPPOSED TO FILTER.

14:54.417 --> 14:57.083
OH, JUST SAY IT.
OKAY. THIS IS
THE BABY THING, RIGHT?

14:57.125 --> 15:00.709
SHE TOLD YOU SHE WANTS A BABY,
AND YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING,

15:00.750 --> 15:03.625
AND EVEN THOUGH SHE TOLD YOU
NOT TO SAY ANYTHING,

15:03.667 --> 15:07.500
SHE'S MAD THAT YOU DIDN'T
SAY ANYTHING, AND SO NOW SH--
AH. FILTER.

15:07.542 --> 15:10.000
I HAVE GOT TO GET
MY OWN LIFE.

15:12.083 --> 15:13.875
(speaks indistinctly)

15:13.917 --> 15:15.041
(sighs)

15:15.083 --> 15:17.625
MY 15-YEAR-OLD PATIENT--
JUSTIN--

15:17.667 --> 15:20.375
GAINED 300 POUNDS
IN 3 YEARS,

15:20.417 --> 15:22.792
AND MOMMY AND DADDY WERE
TOO BUSY TO NOTICE.

15:22.834 --> 15:25.333
SO YOU'RE BLAMING
THE PARENTS?
YOU WOULDN'T?

15:25.375 --> 15:27.625
WELL, IN ALL FAIRNESS,
JUSTIN IS THE ONE

15:27.667 --> 15:30.417
PUTTING THE FOOD IN HIS MOUTH.
WELL, NO, I GET
THAT HE'S EATING,

15:30.458 --> 15:33.750
BUT THE PARENTS
LET IT GET TOO FAR.
(Violet and Sheldon) SO DID HE.

15:33.792 --> 15:35.625
WHOA.

15:35.667 --> 15:37.750
SHRINK MIND MELD.
CREEPY.

15:37.792 --> 15:40.041
GIVE ME BACK MY FRIES.
COME ON. COME ON. COME ON.
HEY, THERE SHE IS.
THERE SHE IS. HI.

15:40.083 --> 15:42.667
OH, HEY. HEY.
OH, HEY.

15:42.709 --> 15:44.667
HOW'S SHE DOING?

15:44.709 --> 15:46.750
SWEETIE.

15:46.792 --> 15:49.542
YEAH.

15:49.583 --> 15:51.667
HEY. HOW YOU DOING?

15:51.709 --> 15:53.667
OH, FIRST DAY
OF THE REST OF MY LIFE.

15:53.709 --> 15:55.041
FEEL GOOD?

15:55.083 --> 15:57.667
WHAT DOESN'T KILL YOU
MAKES YOU STRONGER.

16:00.667 --> 16:03.041
YOU SAW THAT, RIGHT?
IT'S NOT JUST ME? YOU SAW THAT?

16:03.083 --> 16:05.041
THE CLICHéS--
SHE ONLY SPEAKS IN CLICHéS.

16:05.083 --> 16:07.500
SHE'S GOT A MILLION OF 'EM.
AND THE SMILEY THING?

16:07.542 --> 16:09.041
WELL, SHE'S CERTAINLY...
CHIPPER.

16:09.083 --> 16:11.542
BUT CHARLOTTE'S NOT
A SMILEY PERSON.
EXACTLY.

16:11.583 --> 16:13.583
WELL, IT'S A--IT'S
A COPING MECHANISM, COOP.

16:13.625 --> 16:15.959
OKAY, BUT SHE'S NOT COPING.

16:16.000 --> 16:17.500
WHAT DO I DO?

16:17.542 --> 16:20.000
(fries rustle against paper)

16:20.041 --> 16:22.542
MM-HMM. WHERE'S
YOUR MIND MELD NOW, BITCHES?

16:22.583 --> 16:24.583
(crunches)

16:24.625 --> 16:28.583
HOW MUCH DID YOU PAY EMILY
TO GET HER TUBES TIED?

16:28.625 --> 16:33.000
SHE SAID YES TO $250.
I WOULD'VE GONE HIGHER.

16:33.041 --> 16:35.959
PETE, COMPLETELY UNETHICAL.
THERE ARE NONPROFITS
IN ALL 50 STATES

16:36.000 --> 16:38.041
OFFERING DRUG-ADDICTED WOMEN
FINANCIAL INCENTIVES

16:38.083 --> 16:41.041
TO HAVE THEIR TUBES TIED.
YEAH, BUT WE DON'T WORK
FOR THOSE ORGANIZATIONS.

16:41.083 --> 16:43.542
WE'RE DOCTORS.
AND THERE ARE THREE MILLION
CASES OF CHILD ABUSE A YEAR.

16:43.583 --> 16:46.041
DRUG AND ALCOHOL ABUSE

16:46.083 --> 16:48.041
ARE A CONTRIBUTING FACTOR
IN MOST OF THEM.

16:48.083 --> 16:50.792
USUALLY YOU'RE MORE PRACTICAL
THAN THIS.
EMILY ISN'T JUST
SOME STATISTIC.

16:50.834 --> 16:53.542
SHE'S A WOMAN, OKAY, WHO COULD
WAKE UP TEN YEARS FROM NOW,

16:53.583 --> 16:55.083
STILL CLEAN AND SOBER,

16:55.125 --> 16:57.709
AND WISH THAT SHE COULD
HAVE ANOTHER CHILD.

16:57.750 --> 16:59.417
OKAY, LOOK, I FULLY RECOGNIZE

16:59.458 --> 17:01.917
THAT WHAT WE'RE DOING IS
UNETHICAL, POSSIBLY ILLEGAL.

17:01.959 --> 17:04.834
I UNDERSTAND THAT. BUT YOU
KNOW ME. YOU KNOW VIOLET.

17:04.875 --> 17:06.792
SHE'S THE ONE
THAT CAN'T STOP HERSELF

17:06.834 --> 17:10.333
FROM HELPING CRIMINALS,
PEDOPHILES, YOU NAME IT.

17:10.375 --> 17:13.041
IF THE TWO OF US ARE SAYING
THAT EMILY IS A LOST CAUSE,

17:13.083 --> 17:15.041
DOESN'T THAT
TELL YOU SOMETHING?

17:16.917 --> 17:20.583
(women speaking indistinctly)

17:20.625 --> 17:22.125
YES.
(Violet) HI.

17:22.166 --> 17:25.041
HI, BABY.
(speaking gibberish)

17:25.083 --> 17:27.041
I DIDN'T REALIZE
THIS WAS A PLAY DATE.

17:27.083 --> 17:29.041
OH, I GAVE MAYA
THE NIGHT OFF.

17:29.083 --> 17:31.041
(baby talk voice) AREN'T YOU?
YOU'RE SO SMART.

17:31.083 --> 17:32.750
SHE IS SUPER SMART.

17:32.792 --> 17:34.417
(inhales and speaks gibberish)

17:34.458 --> 17:36.250
YES. YES, YOU'RE SO SMART.

17:36.291 --> 17:39.041
(all laugh)
ARE YOU TIRED, TOO?
A LITTLE--

17:39.083 --> 17:41.041
WELL, IT'S BECAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
RUN THE WORLD SOMEDAY.

17:41.083 --> 17:43.375
I KNOW.
IT'S TRUE.

17:43.417 --> 17:46.041
(Violet) ALL RIGHT, IT'S MY
TURN. MY TURN, MY TURN, MY TURN.

17:46.083 --> 17:48.667
(Addison)
THAT'S YOUR AUNTIE VI. YEAH.
(baby talk voice) OH, I MISS
LUCAS BEING THIS LITTLE.

17:48.709 --> 17:50.792
IS CHARLOTTE COMING?
(normal voice) NO.
SHE DECLINED, BUT GRACEFULLY.

17:50.834 --> 17:53.166
YES, SHE'S SPEAKING
IN BUMPER STICKER SLOGANS,

17:53.208 --> 17:55.041
WHICH EITHER MEANS
SHE'S INTERNALIZED

17:55.083 --> 17:57.583
THE HELP
THAT WE'VE BEEN OFFERING HER...
OR WE NEED START

17:57.625 --> 18:00.041
PLANNING ESCAPE ROUTES
IN CASE SHE GOES POSTAL.

18:00.083 --> 18:02.208
OKAY, OKAY, MY TURN AGAIN.
COME ON.
ALL RIGHT.

18:02.250 --> 18:05.500
(speaks gibberish, baby talk
voice) YES, THE SWEETEST GIRL.

18:05.542 --> 18:08.375
HI. HI.
HI. THERE YOU ARE.
THERE YOU ARE.

18:08.417 --> 18:10.667
HI, SWEETIE.
OH, SHE IS SO GORGEOUS.

18:10.709 --> 18:15.291
YES, YOU ARE.
YOU ARE GORGEOUS, LITTLE GIRL.

18:15.333 --> 18:16.875
(laughing)

18:16.917 --> 18:18.667
OKAY, THAT'S IT.

18:18.709 --> 18:20.667
(Violet, normal voice)
WHERE YOU GOING?
NO OFFENSE,

18:20.709 --> 18:22.917
BUT I DID NOT COME HERE
FOR "THE VAGINA MONOLOGUES."

18:22.959 --> 18:25.500
(Addison) WHAT?
WHAT?

18:25.542 --> 18:27.542
(laughs)
(laughing) OH, NOT
"THE VAGINA MONOLOGUES."

18:27.583 --> 18:30.250
DID YOU EVER THINK
WE'D BE THESE WOMEN--

18:30.291 --> 18:32.458
PASSING AROUND A BABY
LIKE IT'S GOOD DRUGS?

18:32.500 --> 18:35.041
BEING THE KIND OF WOMEN THAT
WOMEN LIKE AMELIA RUN FROM?

18:35.083 --> 18:37.709
I WAS ALWAYS,
ALWAYS THIS WOMAN.
(Olivia babbles)

18:37.750 --> 18:40.417
(normal voice) I WANT A BABY.

18:40.458 --> 18:43.083
(baby talk voice)
YES, I DO. I DO.

18:43.125 --> 18:46.375
(normal voice) IT'S PROBABLY
NOT GONNA HAPPEN FOR ME, THOUGH.

18:46.417 --> 18:48.375
(Olivia babbling)
NO, IT'S NOT.

18:48.417 --> 18:50.667
I HAVE BAD OVARIES
AND ONE SAD--

18:50.709 --> 18:52.250
(Olivia babbles)
YES...

18:52.291 --> 18:54.250
(laughs) ONE SAD, LONELY EGG,

18:54.291 --> 18:57.041
AND SAM...

18:57.083 --> 18:58.500
NO.

18:58.542 --> 19:00.625
GO FOR IT.

19:00.667 --> 19:02.000
(chuckles)

19:02.041 --> 19:03.041
(babbles)

19:03.083 --> 19:05.792
"EAT PRAY LOVE."
(laughs)

19:05.834 --> 19:08.583
I DON'T THINK SAM WANTS
ANY MORE CHILDREN.
(liquid pours)

19:08.625 --> 19:10.667
HAVE ONE WITHOUT HIM.

19:10.709 --> 19:12.959
I WANT TO HAVE ONE
WITH HIM.

19:13.000 --> 19:15.166
(baby talk voice)
I DO. YES, I DO.

19:15.208 --> 19:17.166
WELL, THE MAN MAKES
REALLY GOOD BABIES.

19:17.208 --> 19:19.041
MY TURN. (laughs)
COME HERE, SWEETIE.

19:19.083 --> 19:21.500
THERE YOU GO.
THERE YOU ARE.
THERE YOU GO.

19:21.542 --> 19:23.500
YEAH. HELLO, SWEETIE.
HELLO.

19:23.542 --> 19:25.208
(men talking
and laughing indistinctly)

19:25.250 --> 19:27.208
(Cooper)
I WAS GOOD AT IT, TOO.

19:27.250 --> 19:30.125
HEY, COME ON, GUYS. I TOLD YOU
NOT TO LIGHT 'EM.

19:30.166 --> 19:32.333
COME ON.
THEY'RE CUBAN.

19:32.375 --> 19:34.583
WELL, WE CERTAINLY WOULDN'T
WANT TO LET CASTRO DOWN.

19:34.625 --> 19:36.583
I COULD HAVE
AN ASTHMA ATTACK.

19:36.625 --> 19:38.959
I WILL BE THE FIRST TO STICK
AN EpiPen IN YOUR THIGH.

19:39.000 --> 19:41.041
OH, GOD. FINE.
NO CIGARS. I'M DEALING.

19:41.083 --> 19:43.083
HELLO, MEN.

19:43.125 --> 19:44.709
(door closes)
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

19:44.750 --> 19:46.709
UTERUSES NEXT DOOR
BE CRAZY.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.208
ANY OBJECTIONS?

19:48.250 --> 19:50.750
(Matt Duncan) ♪ NO LOVELORN
PRINCE WOULD EVER DARE... ♪

19:50.792 --> 19:53.125
WHY ARE YOU LOOKING AT COOPER?
W-WHY IS SHE LOOKING AT COOPER?

19:53.166 --> 19:56.041
COOPER TOLD ME
TO STAY AWAY FROM HIM,

19:56.083 --> 19:58.041
WHICH IS ALL I'M GOING TO SAY,
BECAUSE FOR ONCE...

19:58.083 --> 20:00.208
YOU ARE FILTERING.
I AM FILTERING.

20:00.250 --> 20:02.041
AH.
YOU GOT MONEY?

20:02.083 --> 20:03.458
HARD CASH.

20:03.500 --> 20:05.250
♪ AMBIVALENT IN C ♪

20:05.291 --> 20:06.959
WELCOME TO THE GAME.

20:07.000 --> 20:10.583
SO WHAT ARE WE TALKING ABOUT--
CHICKS, BOOBS...

20:10.625 --> 20:12.583
(laughs)
CHICKS AND THEIR BOOBS?

20:12.625 --> 20:14.750
(laughs)
(Pete)
WE WERE TALKING ABOUT CIGARS.

20:14.792 --> 20:17.542
BEFORE THAT, WE WERE
TALKING ABOUT BABIES.
WHAT?

20:17.583 --> 20:20.583
(Sheldon) ADDISON WANTS A BABY.
WHICH ISN'T SURPRISING,
THE WAY SHE TOOK TO LUCAS.

20:20.625 --> 20:23.250
WHAT DO YOU WANT, SAM?
(Sam) I WANT
TO MAKE ADDISON HAPPY, BUT, UH,

20:23.291 --> 20:25.041
I'VE ALREADY DONE
THE DADDY THING.

20:25.083 --> 20:26.875
SO DOES THAT MAKE ME SELFISH?

20:26.917 --> 20:29.041
AM I--AM I SELF--
AM I BEING SELFISH?

20:29.083 --> 20:31.083
NO. LIFE SUCKS...
SOMETIMES.

20:31.125 --> 20:33.792
YOU DON'T WANT ANOTHER KID.
ADDISON WANTS A KID.

20:33.834 --> 20:36.583
I WANT A KID. CHARLOTTE'S
TOO DAMAGED TO WANT A KID,

20:36.625 --> 20:39.291
OR TOO DAMAGED TO HAVE A KID,
OR TOO DAMAGED TO HAVE THE SEX

20:39.333 --> 20:41.375
THAT MAKES A KID.
OH, MY GOD. YOU ARE MEN--

20:41.417 --> 20:43.041
HOT, INTERESTING MEN.

20:43.083 --> 20:45.041
PLEASE BE DIRTY AND MANLY
AND SEXIST.

20:45.083 --> 20:47.834
GIVE A GIRL A BREAK.
I BEG OF YOU.

20:47.875 --> 20:49.208
♪ BETTER ♪

20:49.250 --> 20:51.083
♪ WHOA, OH, OH, OH, OH ♪

20:51.125 --> 20:53.041
♪ OH, OH, OH ♪

20:53.083 --> 20:54.625
♪ OH, OH ♪

20:54.667 --> 20:56.625
♪ OH ♪

20:56.667 --> 20:59.208
(keys jangle, lock clicks,
door opens)

20:59.250 --> 21:00.792
HEY.

21:00.834 --> 21:03.417
HEY.

21:03.458 --> 21:05.083
HOW WAS YOUR NIGHT?

21:05.125 --> 21:08.041
IT'S ALWAYS DARKEST
BEFORE THE DAWN.

21:08.083 --> 21:10.709
YEAH, I KNOW.
YOU USED THAT ONE ALREADY.

21:10.750 --> 21:12.709
WHAT?

21:12.750 --> 21:16.333
TRY HAPPY DAYS ARE HERE AGAIN
OR TIME HEALS ALL WOUNDS.

21:16.375 --> 21:18.500
OR HOW ABOUT EVERY CLOUD
HAS A SILVER LINING?

21:18.542 --> 21:21.041
BUT NOT IT'S ALWAYS DARKEST
BEFORE THE DAWN.

21:21.083 --> 21:23.834
YOU CAN'T USE IT'S ALWAYS
DARKEST BEFORE THE DAWN

21:23.875 --> 21:25.458
BECAUSE YOU USED THAT ONE
ALREADY.

21:25.500 --> 21:28.750
AND DAMN IT!
YOU USED THAT ONE ALREADY!

21:28.792 --> 21:30.750
(door closes,
lock clicks)

21:30.792 --> 21:33.792
(muffled crying)

21:36.583 --> 21:39.375
CHARLOTTE.

21:39.417 --> 21:41.542
I'M SORRY.
(sniffles)

21:41.583 --> 21:43.333
I'M SO SORRY. PLEASE.

21:43.375 --> 21:45.333
I-I DIDN'T--
I DIDN'T MEAN IT.

21:45.375 --> 21:48.083
I'M SO...

21:48.125 --> 21:50.959
PLEASE.

21:51.000 --> 21:53.375
SWEETIE, I'M SORRY.

21:53.417 --> 21:57.125
(muffled crying)

22:00.208 --> 22:03.583
(Unkle Bob's "Ships on
the Shoreline" playing)

22:03.625 --> 22:06.542
(inhales)

22:06.583 --> 22:08.500
MM.

22:08.542 --> 22:10.041
♪♪♪

22:10.083 --> 22:11.500
MM.

22:11.542 --> 22:13.375
HEY.

22:13.417 --> 22:15.792
♪ ...TO TELL ME
THAT I'M NOT ALONE ♪

22:15.834 --> 22:17.041
(kisses)

22:17.083 --> 22:18.083
MM.

22:18.125 --> 22:19.792
♪ ...SOMEONE TO PICK UP ♪

22:19.834 --> 22:23.041
ARE WE GONNA
TALK ABOUT THIS?

22:23.083 --> 22:25.625
TALK ABOUT WHAT?

22:25.667 --> 22:27.709
THE BABY THING.

22:27.750 --> 22:29.583
♪ OR ALL THAT YOU NEED ♪

22:29.625 --> 22:31.542
♪ WITH SOMEONE... ♪

22:31.583 --> 22:33.542
THERE'S NOTHING
TO TALK ABOUT.

22:33.583 --> 22:35.333
ADDISON--

22:35.375 --> 22:37.500
NO. I GOTTA GET
TO THE HOSPITAL.

22:37.542 --> 22:39.542
I HAVE A C-SECTION TO DO.

22:39.583 --> 22:41.417
ADDISON--

22:41.458 --> 22:43.667
NOT NOW. OKAY?

22:43.709 --> 22:45.458
JUST...

22:45.500 --> 22:47.667
IF YOU'RE GONNA TAKE BABIES
AWAY FROM ME,

22:47.709 --> 22:51.625
JUST... NOT NOW.

22:51.667 --> 22:53.166
♪ SHIPS ON THE SHORELINE ♪

22:53.208 --> 22:54.625
(door closes)

22:54.667 --> 22:56.375
OKAY.
(shower running)

22:56.417 --> 22:57.834
(clicking keyboard keys)

22:57.875 --> 23:00.917
♪ ARE SAILING AWAY ♪

23:00.959 --> 23:02.834
(stops clicking)

23:02.875 --> 23:04.458
♪ I WISH ♪

23:04.500 --> 23:09.125
♪ I HAD MORE TIME ♪

23:09.166 --> 23:11.834
♪ WITH MORE WORDS ♪

23:11.875 --> 23:14.625
♪ TO SAY ♪

23:14.667 --> 23:17.625
♪ AND WHO AM I KIDDING? ♪

23:17.667 --> 23:20.250
♪ I'M BACK IN A BAR ♪

23:20.291 --> 23:22.709
♪ AND THE SHIPS ON ♪

23:22.750 --> 23:24.250
♪ THE SHORELINE ♪

23:24.291 --> 23:26.625
♪ MIX INTO THE STARS ♪

23:26.667 --> 23:29.667
THE D.A. WON'T PROSECUTE
LEE McHENRY.

23:29.709 --> 23:31.417
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

23:31.458 --> 23:34.083
(sighs)
HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT THAT?

23:34.125 --> 23:36.667
CHARLOTTE DOESN'T CARE.

23:36.709 --> 23:39.041
SHE DOESN'T SEEM TO CARE
ABOUT ANYTHING.

23:39.083 --> 23:41.041
I WASN'T
ASKING ABOUT CHARLOTTE.

23:41.083 --> 23:43.041
I WANT TO KNOW
HOW YOU FEEL.

23:43.083 --> 23:45.417
♪ ...THE SHORELINE ♪

23:45.458 --> 23:47.041
UH...

23:47.083 --> 23:51.208
♪ ARE SAILING AWAY ♪

23:51.250 --> 23:53.041
YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:53.083 --> 23:55.709
I'M GOOD. (sighs)

23:55.750 --> 23:57.667
I'M GOOD.

23:57.709 --> 23:59.417
♪ ...AS RAIN ♪

23:59.458 --> 24:01.875
COOPER,
IF YOU WANT TO TALK,

24:01.917 --> 24:03.834
I'LL KEEP IT CONFIDENTIAL.

24:03.875 --> 24:05.959
NOPE. I'M GREAT.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.041
ARE YOU?

24:08.083 --> 24:09.500
YEAH.

24:09.542 --> 24:11.500
ALWAYS DARKEST
BEFORE THE DAWN.

24:11.542 --> 24:13.041
RIGHT?

24:13.083 --> 24:14.667
♪ SAILING AWAY ♪

24:14.709 --> 24:17.667
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH ♪

24:17.709 --> 24:20.875
♪ SAILING AWAY ♪

24:20.917 --> 24:23.667
♪ OH, OH, OH, OH ♪

24:23.709 --> 24:27.750
♪ OH, OH, OH ♪

24:27.792 --> 24:30.542
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL, ISN'T SHE?

24:30.583 --> 24:33.542
YES, SHE IS.

24:33.583 --> 24:35.750
♪♪♪

24:35.792 --> 24:37.750
I DIDN'T TIE HER TUBES.

24:37.792 --> 24:39.709
ADDISON--
SHH.

24:39.750 --> 24:42.250
(lowered voice) ADDISON,
SHE SIGNED THE CONSENT FORM.

24:42.291 --> 24:44.041
SHE DIDN'T WANT IT.
YOU DID.

24:44.083 --> 24:46.375
YOU WANTED THIS FOR HER,
AND I...

24:46.417 --> 24:49.542
WE CAN'T JUST PAY SOMEONE
TO TIE THEIR TUBES,

24:49.583 --> 24:51.083
OR AT LEAST I CAN'T.

24:51.125 --> 24:53.000
WE'LL GET ANOTHER DOCTOR
TO DO IT.

24:53.041 --> 24:55.041
YOU'D DO THAT TO ME?
REALLY?

24:55.083 --> 24:58.125
TO YOU? UH, PARDON
THE SHRINK IN ME, BUT--

24:58.166 --> 25:01.083
VIOLET, SHE WANTS
TO TURN HER LIFE AROUND

25:01.125 --> 25:03.125
BECAUSE OF THIS CHILD.
SHE TOLD ME THAT.

25:03.166 --> 25:05.709
SHE CAN DO IT. SHE JUST NEEDS
HELP AND SUPPORT,

25:05.750 --> 25:08.625
WHICH IS WHAT THE SHRINK
IN YOU SHOULD BE GIVING HER.

25:08.667 --> 25:11.333
YOU'RE JUST BANGING YOUR HEAD
AGAINST THE WALL.
YEAH? WELL, IT'S MY HEAD.

25:11.375 --> 25:13.750
TALK TO HER.

25:13.792 --> 25:15.792
DO THIS FOR ME.

25:15.834 --> 25:18.333
♪ I WISH I... ♪

25:18.375 --> 25:21.333
OKAY. I'LL DO IT.

25:21.375 --> 25:23.792
♪ MORE TIME ♪

25:23.834 --> 25:28.583
♪ AND MORE WORDS TO SAY ♪

25:28.625 --> 25:30.625
♪ BUT I'LL ♪

25:30.667 --> 25:32.000
♪ BE ♪

25:32.041 --> 25:34.041
♪ RIGHT ♪

25:34.083 --> 25:38.583
♪ AS RAIN ♪

25:38.625 --> 25:42.792
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

25:49.500 --> 25:50.750
HEY.

25:50.792 --> 25:52.750
WHERE'S MY MOM?

25:52.792 --> 25:54.750
SHE HAD TO LEAVE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE,

25:54.792 --> 25:57.041
BUT YOUR DAD'S
IN THE WAITING ROOM.
IS HE MAD AT ME?

25:57.083 --> 26:00.500
NO. NO, HE JUST
HAD TO MAKE SOME CALLS.

26:02.834 --> 26:04.000
(sighs)

26:08.083 --> 26:11.041
I GOT THIS FRIEND.
SOMETHING BAD HAPPENED TO HER,

26:11.083 --> 26:15.709
SOMETHING THAT SHOULDN'T...
HAPPEN TO ANYONE.

26:15.750 --> 26:19.041
AND THE THING I WANT MOST
IN THE WORLD

26:19.083 --> 26:21.041
IS TO HELP HER FEEL BETTER.

26:21.083 --> 26:23.667
BUT SHE WON'T TALK TO ME.

26:23.709 --> 26:25.208
SHE WON'T TALK TO ANYONE.

26:25.250 --> 26:27.208
I CAN TELL SHE'S IN PAIN.

26:27.250 --> 26:29.667
AND I REALLY THINK
THAT IF SHE JUST OPENED UP,

26:29.709 --> 26:31.208
EVERYTHING WOULD CHANGE,

26:31.250 --> 26:33.250
BECAUSE THEN
SHE WOULDN'T BE ALONE.

26:33.291 --> 26:36.250
AND THE TWO OF US TOGETHER,
WE COULD FIGURE OUT WHAT TO DO,

26:36.291 --> 26:38.625
YOU KNOW?

26:38.667 --> 26:41.917
WELL, I'M YOUR FRIEND, TOO,
JUSTIN.

26:41.959 --> 26:45.125
I WANT TO HELP YOU, TOO.

26:49.375 --> 26:53.458
IF I KEEP EATING,
I'LL GET BIGGER...

26:53.500 --> 26:56.041
WHICH IS WHAT I WANTED.

26:56.083 --> 27:00.333
BUT NOW...
IT IS OUT OF CONTROL.

27:03.500 --> 27:05.458
WHY WOULD YOU WANT THAT?

27:05.500 --> 27:08.291
(crying) I JUST...

27:13.834 --> 27:17.417
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO GET TOUCHED ANYMORE.

27:19.792 --> 27:21.709
(cries)

27:23.959 --> 27:25.750
DR. FREEDMAN.

27:31.083 --> 27:33.125
...HIS BLOOD SUGAR SLOWLY

27:33.166 --> 27:35.041
SO THAT HE COMES OUT--
UGH!

27:35.083 --> 27:37.500
COOPER!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? STOP IT!
(grunting)

27:37.542 --> 27:40.041
COOP! WOULD SOMEBODY
PLEASE HELP ME? STOP IT!

27:40.083 --> 27:42.792
GET OFF OF HIM!
COOPER, GET OFF OF HIM!
LET GO OF ME!

27:42.834 --> 27:44.500
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME!
LET HIM GO.

27:44.542 --> 27:48.959
YOU SON OF A BITCH!
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH YOU?!

27:52.083 --> 27:53.542
NOT YOUR SMARTEST MOVE,
COOP.

27:53.583 --> 27:56.041
THAT BASTARD
HAS BEEN ABUSING JUSTIN.

27:56.083 --> 27:58.041
YOU CAN'T HIT PEOPLE,
NO MATTER WHAT.

27:58.083 --> 28:00.041
REALLY? SO AFTER WHAT
BRUCE HAS BEEN DOING,

28:00.083 --> 28:03.000
YOU'RE OKAY
WITH JUST DOING NOTHING?
(knock on door)

28:03.041 --> 28:05.583
BRUCE IS ON THE PHONE
WITH HIS LAWYER RIGHT NOW.

28:05.625 --> 28:07.583
HE'S GONNA SLAP YOU
AND THE HOSPITAL

28:07.625 --> 28:09.333
WITH A MAJOR LAWSUIT.

28:09.375 --> 28:11.208
(sighs) OH, CRAP.

28:11.250 --> 28:13.625
(voice breaks) I DO NOT
NEED THIS RIGHT NOW.

28:13.667 --> 28:15.583
OKAY.

28:15.625 --> 28:18.417
OKAY, OKAY.
I'LL GO MAKE NICE.

28:18.458 --> 28:20.875
I'LL CLEAN IT UP.
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

28:20.917 --> 28:22.041
COOPER--

28:22.083 --> 28:23.625
I'LL HANDLE IT.

28:23.667 --> 28:26.792
DON'T WORRY, SWEETHEART.
I'LL--I'LL FIX IT, OKAY?

28:31.083 --> 28:32.667
(door closes)

28:32.709 --> 28:35.667
CHARLOTTE?

28:35.709 --> 28:39.375
CHARLOTTE, ARE YOU OKAY?

28:39.417 --> 28:41.667
NO.

28:41.709 --> 28:43.667
BUT I'M TRYING TO BE...

28:43.709 --> 28:46.792
(exhales) FOR COOPER.

28:46.834 --> 28:49.709
HE NEEDS ME TO BE OKAY.

28:49.750 --> 28:52.000
BUT HE HATES ME NOW,
OR RESENTS ME, OR...

28:52.041 --> 28:54.041
I DON'T KNOW.

28:54.083 --> 28:58.041
CHARLOTTE, I AM SO SORRY
THIS HAPPENED TO YOU.

28:58.083 --> 29:00.041
NOTHING LIKE BEING RAPED

29:00.083 --> 29:02.500
TO MAKE YOUR DAY
ALL SHINY AND BRIGHT.

29:02.542 --> 29:05.500
CHARLOTTE, I'M GONNA
TELL YOU THIS AHEAD OF TIME

29:05.542 --> 29:07.625
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE SURPRISED,

29:07.667 --> 29:09.625
BUT, UM, I'M GONNA HUG YOU.

29:09.667 --> 29:12.166
STAND UP.
YOU DON'T NEED TO DO--

29:12.208 --> 29:14.417
CHARLOTTE KING,
I AM GOING TO HUG YOU.

29:14.458 --> 29:16.542
STAND UP.

29:39.375 --> 29:41.834
(voice breaking)
I WON'T LET HIM TOUCH ME.

29:41.875 --> 29:44.709
IT'S OKAY.

29:44.750 --> 29:46.625
HE'S GONNA LEAVE ME.

29:46.667 --> 29:48.417
NO, NO, NO.

29:48.458 --> 29:50.500
HE IS NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

29:50.542 --> 29:53.041
AND IF HE DOES,
YOU'LL HAVE ME.

29:53.083 --> 29:55.542
(chuckles)

29:55.583 --> 29:58.875
WELL, ACCORDING TO THE D.A.,
I LIKE MY SEX KINKY.

29:58.917 --> 30:01.000
YOU GONNA GO ALL LESBIAN

30:01.041 --> 30:04.458
AND DRESS UP...
(chuckles) IN LATEX FOR ME?

30:04.500 --> 30:05.667
ABSOLUTELY.

30:05.709 --> 30:09.709
(laughs)

30:09.750 --> 30:12.458
(sniffles)

30:12.500 --> 30:14.291
(cries)

30:14.333 --> 30:16.041
IT'S OKAY.

30:16.083 --> 30:18.041
(continues crying)

30:18.083 --> 30:19.709
YOU'RE OKAY.

30:19.750 --> 30:22.583
OKAY.

30:22.625 --> 30:24.458
HEY.
HEY.

30:24.500 --> 30:27.291
THESE PAIN MEDS ARE GOOD.
THANKS, DOC.

30:27.333 --> 30:29.500
WOULD YOU LIKE TO SEE
YOUR BABY?

30:29.542 --> 30:32.041
IS DR. WILDER HERE?
IS HE COMING?

30:35.875 --> 30:37.709
EMILY, UM...

30:37.750 --> 30:40.417
DR. MONTGOMERY
DIDN'T TIE YOUR TUBES.

30:40.458 --> 30:44.041
WHAT?
SHE DOESN'T THINK
THAT SHE SHOULD TIE YOUR TUBES

30:44.083 --> 30:46.125
JUST BECAUSE DR. WILDER
PAID YOU MONEY.

30:46.166 --> 30:49.083
I'VE GOT RIGHTS.
I SIGNED A CONSENT FORM.

30:49.125 --> 30:51.959
YOU GOTTA DO IT.
I SIGNED A CONSENT FORM.

30:52.000 --> 30:55.333
I NEED THAT MONEY.
VIOLET, WHAT--

30:55.375 --> 30:59.041
(money rustling)
OKAY, WHAT IF I PAID YOU $250
FOR NO REASON?

30:59.083 --> 31:02.667
WOULD YOU STILL
WANT YOUR TUBES TIED?

31:02.709 --> 31:06.959
WOULD I GET ANOTHER $250
IF I DID?

31:07.000 --> 31:08.750
NO.

31:08.792 --> 31:12.333
(exhales)
YOU STILL WANT THE SURGERY?
DO YOU?

31:12.375 --> 31:15.750
NO!
WHAT IF I OFFERED YOU $250
TO GIVE ME YOUR BABY?

31:15.792 --> 31:17.542
SHE'S A HEALTHY BABY.
SHE'S A GOOD ONE.

31:17.583 --> 31:20.041
SHE'S A GOOD BABY.
VIOLET. THAT'S ENOUGH.
COME ON. LET'S GO.

31:20.083 --> 31:22.458
SHE'S WORTH WAY MORE
THAN $250.

31:22.500 --> 31:25.000
$500. I'LL SELL HER
FOR $500.

31:28.083 --> 31:30.917
I THINK WE'RE DONE HERE.

31:32.417 --> 31:35.875
HEY, WHERE'S MY MONEY?
WHERE'S MY MONEY?!

31:35.917 --> 31:37.709
(sighs)
(door closes)

31:37.750 --> 31:39.667
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND THIS.

31:39.709 --> 31:41.208
I KNOW YOU THINK

31:41.250 --> 31:43.208
I'M BEING CALLOUS
AND UNFEELING AND AWFUL.

31:43.250 --> 31:46.291
BUT I HAVE BEEN DEALING
WITH EMILY

31:46.333 --> 31:49.250
FOR SIX YEARS.

31:49.291 --> 31:51.166
I BELIEVE PEOPLE CAN CHANGE.

31:51.208 --> 31:53.041
YOU KNOW I DO.

31:53.083 --> 31:55.834
BUT THAT WOMAN...

31:55.875 --> 31:58.458
ADDISON, SHE MAKES ME
BELIEVE IN HELL.

31:58.500 --> 32:01.500
SHE MAKES ME NEED TO BELIEVE
IN HELL

32:01.542 --> 32:04.000
SO THAT SHE CAN GO THERE.

32:05.917 --> 32:08.291
BUT I AM...

32:08.333 --> 32:11.792
SORRY... I MEAN.

32:18.500 --> 32:20.750
DR. FREEDMAN--

32:20.792 --> 32:24.542
NO, NO, I-I DON'T WANT YOU
ANYWHERE NEAR ME OR MY SON.

32:24.583 --> 32:26.542
I'M HAVING YOU ARRESTED.
FINE, WE CAN SHARE A CELL,

32:26.583 --> 32:29.500
BECAUSE I AM TELLING THE POLICE
WHAT YOU'VE BEEN DOING TO HIM.

32:29.542 --> 32:33.458
YOU SHOULD LEAVE,
DR. FREEDMAN.
JUSTIN, JUSTIN, I PROMISE YOU,
HE WILL NEVER TOUCH YOU AGAIN.

32:33.500 --> 32:36.041
NO, IT'S--IT'S NOT...

32:36.083 --> 32:39.667
I-I DIDN'T MEAN
IT WAS MY DAD.

32:39.709 --> 32:42.583
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

32:42.625 --> 32:44.041
JUSTIN,

32:44.083 --> 32:46.917
DON'T WORRY ABOUT THIS, BABY.

32:46.959 --> 32:49.709
IT'S OKAY, HONEY.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

32:49.750 --> 32:52.041
IT'S OKAY, BABY.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THIS, OKAY?

32:52.083 --> 32:54.542
I'LL FIX EVERYTHING.
PAM?

32:54.583 --> 32:56.041
HE'S JUST CONFUSED.

32:56.083 --> 32:58.583
IT'S ALL THESE MEDICATIONS
THAT THEY HAVE HIM ON.

32:58.625 --> 33:00.667
PAM, SIT DOWN.

33:02.500 --> 33:05.000
UH, YOU CAN'T--
SIT DOWN.

33:07.750 --> 33:11.041
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

33:11.083 --> 33:15.083
HOW COULD--HOW COULD YOU
DO THAT TO OUR SON?

33:18.542 --> 33:20.667
HE LOVES ME.

33:24.208 --> 33:26.208
BRUCE! BRUCE! BRUCE! COME ON.

33:26.250 --> 33:27.709
CALL SECURITY! SECURITY!

33:27.750 --> 33:32.583
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY. OKAY.

33:35.417 --> 33:37.750
(monitor beeping rhythmically)

33:37.792 --> 33:39.750
JUSTIN,
THIS IS DR. WALLACE.

33:39.792 --> 33:41.709
HE'S A THERAPIST,
AND, UH,

33:41.750 --> 33:44.208
HE'S HERE TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT, UH...

33:44.250 --> 33:47.041
YOUR FEELINGS.

33:47.083 --> 33:49.041
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

33:49.083 --> 33:51.583
BECAUSE TALKING ABOUT IT
GOT YOUR MOM ARRESTED?

33:51.625 --> 33:54.458
IT WAS MY FAULT.
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

33:54.500 --> 33:56.458
WHAT YOUR MOTHER DID TO YOU,

33:56.500 --> 34:00.041
NO ONE SHOULD EVER
HAVE TO LIVE WITH THAT.

34:00.083 --> 34:02.083
BUT WE CAN TALK ABOUT THAT.

34:02.125 --> 34:05.583
WE CAN TALK ABOUT
ANYTHING YOU WANT.
YOU WANT ME NOT TO BE FAT.

34:05.625 --> 34:07.208
FAT WAS YOUR PROTECTION.

34:07.250 --> 34:09.250
THAT WAS SMART,
AND IT WAS BRAVE,

34:09.291 --> 34:12.792
BUT, JUSTIN, YOU DON'T
HAVE TO BE PROTECTED ANYMORE.

34:12.834 --> 34:15.834
ALL RIGHT? YOU'RE SAFE.

34:18.834 --> 34:21.000
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO STOP.

34:22.458 --> 34:24.083
(footsteps approach)

34:26.542 --> 34:28.041
DAD, I'M SORRY. I--

34:28.083 --> 34:29.583
DON'T. PLEASE.

34:29.625 --> 34:33.458
I-I DIDN'T KNOW, JUSTIN,
WHAT YOUR MOTHER...

34:35.500 --> 34:37.375
I DIDN'T SEE IT.

34:37.417 --> 34:39.000
IT'S OKAY.

34:39.041 --> 34:41.000
(Sheldon)
DON'T TELL HIM THAT.

34:41.041 --> 34:43.750
DON'T BURY IT.
TELL HIM THE TRUTH.

34:47.750 --> 34:49.417
WHY?

34:49.458 --> 34:53.041
YOU'RE MY FATHER.
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO PROTECT ME.

34:53.083 --> 34:56.041
WHY DIDN'T YOU PROTECT ME?

34:56.083 --> 34:59.041
♪♪♪

34:59.083 --> 35:01.542
I LOVE YOU.

35:01.583 --> 35:03.750
AND I FAILED.

35:03.792 --> 35:06.709
AND I HOPE THAT SOMEDAY...

35:06.750 --> 35:08.667
♪♪♪

35:08.709 --> 35:11.959
(crying)
CAN YOU FORGIVE ME?

35:12.000 --> 35:15.667
♪♪♪

35:18.875 --> 35:21.709
(woman) ♪ STOP ME ♪

35:21.750 --> 35:23.542
♪ IF YOU'VE HEARD ♪

35:23.583 --> 35:27.750
♪ THIS ONE ♪

35:27.792 --> 35:30.291
THIS IS YOUR BABY.

35:30.333 --> 35:32.291
YOU CAN HOLD HER
IF YOU WANT.

35:32.333 --> 35:34.291
I CAN TEACH YOU
HOW TO FEED HER.

35:34.333 --> 35:37.000
I CAN GET YOU TO A SHELTER,

35:37.041 --> 35:41.709
GET HELP FROM SOCIAL SERVICES.

35:41.750 --> 35:43.375
OR...

35:43.417 --> 35:45.959
I HAVE $1,000 CASH.

35:46.000 --> 35:47.917
YOU CAN TAKE IT AND...

35:47.959 --> 35:49.542
SIGN THESE PAPERS

35:49.583 --> 35:53.750
RELINQUISHING PARENTAL RIGHTS
TO YOUR BABY.

35:53.792 --> 35:56.166
♪ FALL ENDLESSLY ♪

35:56.208 --> 35:58.792
CAN I GET MORE?

35:58.834 --> 36:00.792
NO. $1,000

36:00.834 --> 36:03.500
OR I WALK.

36:03.542 --> 36:06.959
♪ NOTHING IS HOW... ♪

36:07.000 --> 36:08.750
GIVE ME THE MONEY.

36:08.792 --> 36:10.083
(pen clatters)

36:10.125 --> 36:13.291
YOU DON'T EVEN WANT TO SEE HER?
SHE'S AMAZING.

36:13.333 --> 36:15.041
GIVE ME MY MONEY.

36:15.083 --> 36:18.583
♪♪♪

36:28.959 --> 36:32.333
♪ HERE ON THE GROUND ♪

36:32.375 --> 36:35.375
♪ THE STARS FALL ♪

36:35.417 --> 36:38.333
♪ FALL ENDLESSLY ♪

36:38.375 --> 36:42.542
(babies fussing)

36:42.583 --> 36:44.041
(Sam) ADDISON.

36:44.083 --> 36:46.750
♪ BACK HERE AT HOME ♪

36:46.792 --> 36:48.375
(crying) SHE'S SO LITTLE.

36:48.417 --> 36:50.041
YEAH, I KNOW.

36:50.083 --> 36:53.333
SHE HAS NO ONE.

36:53.375 --> 36:55.041
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

36:55.083 --> 36:56.333
(sniffles)

36:56.375 --> 36:58.041
THE WOMAN FROM SOCIAL SERVICE

36:58.083 --> 37:01.667
IS BRINGING HER NEW PARENTS
TO MEET HER.

37:01.709 --> 37:03.542
♪ BEING HERE... ♪

37:03.583 --> 37:06.166
THIS COULD BE OUR BABY.

37:06.208 --> 37:07.792
BUT IT'S NOT.

37:07.834 --> 37:11.041
BUT IT COULD BE.

37:11.083 --> 37:12.667
(whispers) BUT IT'S NOT.

37:12.709 --> 37:14.667
♪♪♪

37:14.709 --> 37:17.208
(normal voice) YOU WANT TO HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION NOW?

37:17.250 --> 37:19.667
(sniffles)

37:19.709 --> 37:21.041
OKAY.

37:21.083 --> 37:23.709
♪ IT'S ON OUR SIDE ♪

37:23.750 --> 37:26.667
♪ AND YOUR WORD ♪

37:26.709 --> 37:30.291
WE CAN'T MOVE ACCORDING TO
YOUR BIOLOGICAL CLOCK.

37:30.333 --> 37:32.041
IT'S TOO FAST.

37:32.083 --> 37:33.291
(sighs)

37:33.333 --> 37:35.041
WE JUST GOT STARTED.

37:35.083 --> 37:37.625
(sniffles)

37:37.667 --> 37:39.834
YOU GOTTA GIVE ME SOME TIME.

37:39.875 --> 37:42.041
♪ AND HERE ON THE GROUND ♪

37:42.083 --> 37:43.709
♪ THE STARS FALL ♪

37:43.750 --> 37:45.709
I AM BELIEVING YOU.

37:45.750 --> 37:50.041
♪ ENDLESSLY ♪

37:50.083 --> 37:51.625
♪ YEAH ♪

37:51.667 --> 37:53.041
BELIEVE ME.

37:53.083 --> 37:55.458
♪ AND BACK HERE AT HOME ♪

37:55.500 --> 37:57.041
♪ NOTHING IS ♪

37:57.083 --> 38:04.500
♪ HOW IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE ♪

38:04.542 --> 38:10.709
♪ ALL EXCEPT FOR YOU ♪

38:12.083 --> 38:15.458
♪ BEING HERE ♪

38:15.500 --> 38:18.542
(footsteps approach)

38:18.583 --> 38:24.000
♪ WITH ME ♪

38:25.542 --> 38:28.500
SITTING ALONE IN A DARK ROOM.

38:28.542 --> 38:31.041
I USED TO DO THAT.

38:31.083 --> 38:34.000
THEN AGAIN, I USED TO DOWN
NARCOTICS LIKE CANDY, SO...

38:36.709 --> 38:38.583
COME HERE.

38:41.750 --> 38:43.542
(sighs)

38:43.583 --> 38:46.583
(groans)

38:48.750 --> 38:52.208
CAN I SAY THAT I'M GLAD
WE'RE FRIENDS AGAIN?

38:54.625 --> 38:56.625
(gasps and pants)

38:56.667 --> 39:01.000
I MAY BE EASY, COOPER,
BUT I AM NOT A WHORE.

39:03.083 --> 39:05.583
GO HOME.
GO HOME TO CHARLOTTE.

39:05.625 --> 39:09.041
AND WE WILL PRETEND...
THAT THIS NEVER HAPPENED.

39:09.083 --> 39:11.041
(door opens)

39:13.375 --> 39:16.792
(Sleeping at Last's "Homesick"
playing)

39:19.875 --> 39:22.875
(footsteps approach)

39:22.917 --> 39:26.375
♪♪♪

39:26.417 --> 39:28.583
♪ YOU SPEND YOUR WHOLE LIFE ♪

39:28.625 --> 39:30.166
(groans)

39:30.208 --> 39:33.041
♪ JUST TO REMEMBER ♪

39:33.083 --> 39:34.583
♪ THE SOUND ♪

39:34.625 --> 39:36.083
(Cooper sighs)

39:38.166 --> 39:40.041
♪ WHEN THE WORLD ♪

39:40.083 --> 39:42.041
♪ WAS BRIGHTER ♪

39:42.083 --> 39:47.041
♪ BEFORE WE LEARNED
TO DIM IT DOWN ♪

39:48.875 --> 39:50.417
WHATEVER IT IS,

39:50.458 --> 39:52.125
I CAN HELP.

39:52.166 --> 39:54.542
(sighs)

39:54.583 --> 39:58.709
(clears throat)

39:58.750 --> 40:00.375
(exhales)

40:00.417 --> 40:02.041
MY GIRLFRIEND GETS ATTACKED.

40:02.083 --> 40:04.166
SHE WANTS TO GO HOME,
I TAKE HER HOME.

40:04.208 --> 40:06.500
SHE WANTS TO GO TO WORK,
I DRIVE HER.

40:06.542 --> 40:09.041
I FOUND OUT SHE WASN'T
JUST ATTACKED, SHE WAS RAPED.

40:09.083 --> 40:11.291
SHE TELLS ME SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO I.D. THE GUY,

40:11.333 --> 40:13.291
I SAY,
"OKAY, DON'T I.D. THE GUY."

40:13.333 --> 40:14.792
I'M CHEERFUL, I'M ATTENTIVE,

40:14.834 --> 40:16.875
I MAKE BREAKFAST FOR HER
EVERY MORNING.

40:16.917 --> 40:19.875
MY JOB RIGHT NOW
IS GOOD MAN IN THE STORM.

40:19.917 --> 40:22.041
I GET THAT. I'M GOOD WITH THAT.
I WANT THAT.

40:22.083 --> 40:24.041
♪ OUR RESIGNATION ♪

40:24.083 --> 40:27.417
BUT THE CHARLOTTE
I FELL IN LOVE WITH... IS GONE.

40:27.458 --> 40:29.917
SHE DOESN'T EXIST ANYMORE.

40:29.959 --> 40:34.667
THE LAUGHING, THE SHARING
IN THE GOOD AND BAD OF THE DAY,

40:34.709 --> 40:36.542
HOLDING EACH OTHER--

40:36.583 --> 40:38.333
THAT'S ALL OVER.

40:38.375 --> 40:40.333
IT'S LIKE...
IT'S LIKE SHE'S DEAD.

40:40.375 --> 40:42.041
IT'S LIKE CHARLOTTE IS DEAD,

40:42.083 --> 40:44.041
AND I HAVE
THE GOOD-MAN-IN-THE-STORM JOB.

40:44.083 --> 40:46.041
I AM THE FIANCé OF THE VICTIM.

40:46.083 --> 40:49.500
MY JOB IS TO HOLD UP THE CORPSE
THAT WAS ONCE CHARLOTTE

40:49.542 --> 40:51.500
AND SMILE.

40:51.542 --> 40:53.667
♪♪♪

40:53.709 --> 40:57.917
CAN YOU HELP ME WITH THAT?

40:57.959 --> 41:01.000
♪♪♪

41:03.000 --> 41:04.500
(cell phone ringing)

41:04.542 --> 41:07.500
♪ FLOWERS ARE LASTING ♪

41:07.542 --> 41:09.959
♪ AND WE'RE REBORN UNTESTED ♪

41:10.000 --> 41:11.959
IS IT THE HOSPITAL?

41:12.000 --> 41:13.750
OH! IT'S BIZZY.

41:13.792 --> 41:15.041
(groans)

41:15.083 --> 41:16.667
(sighs)
(rings and beeps)

41:16.709 --> 41:21.542
BIZZY. IT'S THREE HOURS
EARLIER HERE.

41:21.583 --> 41:23.250
♪♪♪

41:23.291 --> 41:24.583
WHAT?

41:24.625 --> 41:27.875
♪ ALL REVELATIONS ♪

41:27.917 --> 41:29.750
♪ COME TO US ♪

41:29.792 --> 41:33.959
♪ IN RECOVERY ♪

41:34.000 --> 41:35.917
♪ CRY WOLF ♪

41:35.959 --> 41:38.792
♪ CRY MERCY ♪

41:38.834 --> 41:42.542
♪ CRY THE NAME OF THE ONE ♪

41:42.583 --> 41:47.041
♪ YOU WERE RAISED
TO BELIEVE ♪

41:47.083 --> 41:50.000
♪ AH, AH ♪

41:50.041 --> 41:51.750
♪ CRY A HEART ♪

41:51.792 --> 41:53.834
♪ CRY YOURSELF TO SLEEP ♪

41:53.875 --> 41:55.834
♪ CRY YOUR STORM ♪

41:55.875 --> 41:57.959
♪ OF TEARS ♪

41:58.000 --> 41:59.500
HELLO, ADDISON.

41:59.542 --> 42:01.667
BIZZY.

42:01.709 --> 42:03.625
WHAT'S GOING ON?

42:03.667 --> 42:05.583
♪♪♪

42:05.625 --> 42:08.083
I NEED YOUR HELP.

42:08.125 --> 42:10.041
♪ ...YOU ♪

42:10.083 --> 42:12.041
♪ IF IT HELPS YOU ♪

42:12.083 --> 42:15.917
♪ BREATHE ♪

42:22.709 --> 42:25.667
♪♪♪
